In this article, President Donald J. Trump issues a proclamation recognizing Mother's Day. He highlights the importance of mothers in our lives and the love, guidance, and support they provide. He acknowledges that mothers play a crucial role in shaping society and passing down wisdom and values to future generations. President Trump encourages all Americans to express their love and respect for their mothers or mother figures and reflect on the significance of motherhood to families, communities, and the nation. He officially designates May 10, 2020, as Mother's Day in the United States.